data.title: Portrait of Ferdinand Jacob Heinrich, Baron von Mueller
data.meta_description: Portrait of Ferdinand Jacob Heinrich, Baron von Mueller. Born 30 June 1825 in Rostock, Germany. Died 10 October 1896 in Melbourne, Australia. Wood engraving, c. 1880. Reasonable condition. Paper slightly soiled and slightly browned. With some faint staining/spotting. Verso: blank. Note: with a biography in French on two separate leafs. Dimensions: 155 x 131 mm. Ferdinand Jacob Heinrich, Baron von Mueller was Physician, Geographer, Botanist, Flemish Botanist, Government botanist for the colony of Victoria by Governor Charles La Trobe, and Director of the Royal Botanic Gardens.
